---
import PageIntro from "../../components/PageIntro.astro";
import { currentStableRelease, packageMetadata, plannedRelease, sourceRepository } from "../../content/site";
import GalleryLayout from "../../layouts/GalleryLayout.astro";
const consumers = [
  ["01", "ComplyEaze", "First controlled public/product surface"],
  ["02", "Axal", "Protected workspace after public foundation proof"],
  ["03", "Pack", "Local-first utility; no taxpayer upload assumption"],
  ["04", "Tools", "Browser-local drafts after bounded tool specs"],
] as const;
---
<GalleryLayout title="Adoption | Sanchika" description="Sanchika consumer order, package artifact method, public and protected boundaries, compatibility, rollback, and open proof gaps.">
  <main id="main-content" class="site-main docs-page" tabindex="-1">
    <PageIntro eyebrow="Adoption" title="Adopt one controlled surface, then prove the boundary." description="Sanchika travels through package entrypoints and reviewed artifacts. Consumers own product copy, authorization, runtime behavior, real evidence, and rollback." meta={`Current stable v${currentStableRelease} · v${plannedRelease} planned, not released`} />
    <section class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="consumer-order-title"><h2 id="consumer-order-title">Known consumer order</h2><ol class="adoption-line">{consumers.map(([step, name, purpose]) => <li><span>{step}</span><strong>{name}</strong><small>{purpose}</small></li>)}</ol></section>
    <section class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="artifact-method-title"><h2 id="artifact-method-title">Package artifact method</h2><div class="doc-grid">{packageMetadata.map((pkg) => <article class="doc-card"><span>{pkg.name}</span><h3>{pkg.entrypoints[0]}</h3><p>Import only package entrypoints. CSS follows token → primitive → pattern order when needed.</p><a href={pkg.docs}>Read package documentation</a></article>)}</div></section>
    <section class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="acquisition-title"><h2 id="acquisition-title">Current acquisition path</h2><div class="doc-grid doc-grid--2"><article class="doc-card"><span>Local-link evaluation</span><h3>Prove a narrow consumer surface first.</h3><p>The packages are not presented as a current public registry release. Link the checked-out package into a controlled consumer, record the mapped files, and keep rollback explicit.</p><a href={`${sourceRepository}/blob/master/docs/adoption-evidence.md`}>Use the adoption evidence record</a></article><article class="doc-card"><span>Packed artifact evaluation</span><h3>Test what a consumer would actually install.</h3><p>Create the repository’s deterministic package tarballs, install those artifacts in the fixture consumer, then run the packed-tarball compatibility lane before proposing adoption.</p><a href={`${sourceRepository}/blob/master/docs/release-policy.md`}>Inspect the artifact policy</a></article></div></section>
    <section class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="adoption-boundary-title"><h2 id="adoption-boundary-title">Public, protected, and compatibility boundaries</h2><div class="doc-grid doc-grid--2"><article class="doc-card"><span>Public first</span><p>Start with a public/product surface that needs no auth, tenant data, document handling, or workspace behavior.</p></article><article class="doc-card"><span>Protected later</span><p>Axal adoption requires real authorization, tenant isolation, persistence, source handling, and audit evidence outside this public gallery.</p></article><article class="doc-card"><span>Compatibility</span><p>Stable package entrypoints and one-release legacy adapters are preserved. This gallery iteration does not change package exports or versions.</p></article><article class="doc-card"><span>Rollback</span><p>Remove the package link, CSS imports, and the single mapped usage. Record changed and rollback files in adoption evidence.</p></article></div></section>
    <section class="doc-section" aria-labelledby="unproven-title"><h2 id="unproven-title">What remains unproven</h2><p>Real consumer adoption remains incomplete. Broad external adoption, every framework adapter, full protected-workspace depth, every assistive technology, and production behavior across all four consumers remain outside this static evidence. See the <a href={`${sourceRepository}/blob/master/docs/adoption-evidence.md`}>adoption evidence template</a> and per-consumer guidance before claiming rollout.</p></section>
  </main>
</GalleryLayout>
